per cent of the overall population),more than three-fourths (77 per cent) of these users were from New Delhi and the capitals of Indian states. Two cities \u2013 Delhi and Mumbai \u2013 alone accounted for more than one-third of all users. Maharashtra, with 453,000 users accounted for 28 per cent of the total. On the other hand, two of India\u2019s most populous states \u2013 Uttar Pradesh and Bihar \u2013 had only 20,000 and 8,000, respectively.6 Clearly, the inadequate spread of connectivity, the per- ceived benefits of connectivity and the cost at which it is available are working against as rapid a spread of the Internet as was seen in the case of radio. With respect to PC penetration, Malaysia leads the nine countries with 14.7 PCs per 100 inhab- itants. All the others have single digit PC pene- tration rates. In fact, Pakistan, India and Vietnam are at the bottom, with the PC penetration rate below 1 per 100 inhabitants.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "44743584-f3c7-4090-8e60-ec87ed31e79a": {"__data__": {"id_": "44743584-f3c7-4090-8e60-ec87ed31e79a", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-2005-promoting-ict-human-development-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Asia-Pacific Human Development 2005: Promoting ICT for Human Development in Asia", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-human-development-2005-promoting-ict-human-development-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash":